</p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The following Conclusions were also placed in the 2012 review:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 16pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">8. Significant further work also remains to increase the transparency of the assessment. Changes already implemented to ensure conclusions reached at the face-to-face assessment and in the decision making process are justified are helpful. However, most importantly, ensuring quality feedback from First-tier Tribunal Judges so both claimant and Decision Maker understand why the initial decision has been changed needs to be urgently addressed. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 16pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">9.  It is essential that all relevant medical and allied evidence about a claimant is available to the DWP Decision Maker at the earliest possible stage in the assessment process. If this can be achieved then Tribunals will be based on Judges and Medical Members considering the same body of evidence as the Decision Maker did. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; widows:0"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">10.Future Independent Reviewers may have different views, but the main issues on which this Independent Reviewer believes the forthcoming year four </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">and five Reviews need to focus attention (include):</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt; widows:0"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 36pt; orphans:0; text-align:justify; text-indent:-36pt; widows:0"><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"></span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">p</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">r</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">v</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">g</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">f</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">b</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">k</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">m</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">c</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">h</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="f